-- Barclays’ Kitei Elected Chairman of Loan Trade Association
-- B y   K r i s t a   G i o v a c c o
-- 2012-01-23T21:30:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-23/barclays-kitei-elected-chairman-of-loan-trade-association.html
Jonathan Kitei, managing director at
Barclays Capital Plc, was elected chairman of the  Loan
Syndications and Trading Association .  Greg Stoeckle of Invesco Ltd., last year’s chairman, and
David Frey of Highbridge Capital Management LLC were named vice
chairmen, the New York-based trade association for the corporate
loan market said today in a statement. Kevin Burke from  GE
Capital  was elected treasurer and Octagon Credit Investor’s
Andrew Gordon was chosen as secretary, the LSTA said.  The other members of the association’s 2012 board of
directors are: John Abate of Silver Point Capital LP, Brian Callahan of Bank of America Corp., Bill Dobson of Deutsche Bank
AG, Austin Garrison of JPMorgan Chase & Co., Kim Harris of
Sankaty Advisors LLC, Leland Hart of BlackRock Inc., Tim Hartshorn of  Fidelity Investments , Mike Henderlong of Morgan
Stanley, Dave Miller of Credit Suisse Group AG, Manish Mital of
Halcyon Asset Management LLC, Dan Norman of ING Groep NV, Craig Russ of Eaton Vance Corp., Tom Stein of Goldman Sachs Group Inc.
and Joe Wilson of Citigroup Inc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krista Giovacco in  New York  at 
 kgiovacco1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Faris Khan at 
 fkhan33@bloomberg.net . 